{"CHIVACHIE":[{"def":"A cavalry raid; hence, a military expedition.","pos":""}],"CHIVALRIC":[{"def":"Relating to chivalry; knightly; chivalrous.","pos":""}],"CHIVALROUS":[{"def":"Pertaining to chivalry or knight-errantry; warlike; heroic; gallant; high-spirited; high-minded; magnanimous.","pos":""}],"CHIVALROUSLY":[{"def":"In a chivalrous manner; gallantly; magnanimously.","pos":""}],"CHIVALRY":[{"def":"A tenure of lands by knight's service; that is, by the condition of a knight's performing service on horseback, or of performing some noble or military service to his lord.","pos":""}],"CHIVE":[{"def":"A filament of a stamen.","pos":""}],"CHIVY":[{"def":"To goad, drive, hunt, throw, or pitch.","pos":""}]}